cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.MM, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper discusses the impact of edge caching on data sponsoring in cellular networks, which involves network infrastructure and user behavior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses game theory to model the interactions between the content provider and the users, which suggests cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with video content, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also considers the impact on the data market, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the security implications of the proposed approach, which could be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
